<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_ae567467-9bb4-4c1e-a0d9-a53f0a63ca86" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>S19C4</sptc><title id="_495224c2-082e-49e6-b21f-98ad00861314">Location of fire control centre</title><archive-num>2019: Spec E1.8: 3</archive-num><subclause id="_5f1046ba-491c-4590-939f-0c6e65d94f47" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_7923f690-0521-46ac-abd0-317375d27b9e">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A fire control centre must be so located in a building that egress from any part of its floor, to a road or <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1385_0.4.0.xml#_b4a20ca6-0197-4381-9e50-85c757fa574f" id="_8b60893e-5c7e-4443-9118-5d840032df3f" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">open space</xref>, does not involve changes in level which in aggregate exceed 300 mm.</p></subclause></clause>